JsonObject - Class in <Unnamed>
A JSON object is one of the following: -Number (integer, floating point, etc) -String (anything enclosed by quotes) -Boolean (true/false), no quotes) -Array (anything in square brackets "[]", comma separated) -Object (anything in curly braces "{}", comma separated) -null (the word "null" without quotes) A subobject is a String object, followed by a semicolon ":", with any valid JSON object following it.
